CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier reads:" Four Car Crash- Druken driving caused this crash, according to the police. Walter Jackson, 46, of 2297 Centre Avenue, was under the influence of liquor, said City Physician Dr. J.R.Donoghue, while operating his car (lower photo) and driving west on Centre Avenue last Friday evening when the automobile struck one driven by Chester Larkins of 17 Torrence Street, and a Centre Avenue radio patrol car (top photo) manned by Patrolman Benjamin Livingston and Albert Mills.  The radio car then was pushed into another car (behind the radio car) driven by Walter W. Brown of 2717 Webster Avenue.  Patrolman Livingston received a possible fracutre of the left arm.  Jackson was held for court on a drunken driving charge by Magistrate J.J. Strba in Traffic Court Monday morning."See file for full discription.
TitMainTitle: Pittsburgh City police car with driver side damage parked in street near F. B. Johanssen and Sons, street no. 1634
